														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-954801">
									

<p>I think it would be cool to do something like Herbertsmithite. It's believed to be a String-net liquid. They were first hypothesised in 1983, and the Foundation is older than that, so it's possible they found out about it before anybody knew what it was.</p>
<p>Of course, it doesn't seem to have any really weird effects.</p>
<p>There's probably several other things like that. I've read about something where someone found out that if you put a current through a certain rock, it glows. It was a really weak LED, but this was before the physics of them were understood.</p>
<p>What would be best would be something that was found shortly after the physics required to understand it were discovered, as this is what it would look like if the Foundation was suppressing it until then.</p>

							</div>

								
					
