														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-954824">
									

<p>Why would they suppress the knowledge of how to make a rock glow and not, say, the construction of nuclear weapons? One of these things is a much greater threat to normalcy than the other, and neither are in any way supernatural phenomena.</p>
<p>If anything, I think it would serve to make the Foundation appear idiotic should they assume that everything not currently understood was in some way paranormal or endeavor to suppress knowledge "just because." The Foundation, in my mind, gets involved <em>after</em> all rational explanation has been ruled out, and <em>not</em> before such has even been attempted.</p>
<p>I would expect the Foundation to thoroughly investigate said glowing rock and then patent LED technology to supplement existing sources of funding, but not suppress knowledge of it at any point.</p>

							</div>

								
